12:
Maybe now you'll be in a listening
mood!
16:
So that sword really can cut through
my power... But how?
20:
Ugh, I can't believe you had
something this strong stowed away.
24:
Wait! Are you really about to leave
your friends behind?
31:
Aegis only needs people who can
carry their own weight. That's all that
matters with us.
37:
What sad lives those people live.
They'll never find salvation as long
as they cling to those beliefs.
44:
I am Sakuya Hoshino. I serve as
leader of the Starsayers.
51:
Alk. Stella. May I have a moment of
your time?
62:
I have the power of clairvoyance—to
make known the unknown.
68:
I would like to offer my thanks, as
well as my sincerest apology.
71:
I asked you here, but I cannot offer
much in the way of hospitality.
79:
You will show respect to Lady
Sakuya—
84:
It's all right. As outsiders, they have
no obligations to me.
86:
Would you clear the room and give
us a moment of privacy?
99:
You said you're clairvoyant? How
much do you know about us, then?
102: You came from beyond this place.
105:
And I knew that you would meet me
here. But that's as far as I saw.
107:
I'd like to ask a question of my own.
You're not working for the Japanese
government, are you?
112: We aren't. We're from another world.
116:
An entirely different world... As I
thought.
119:
Regardless, you are the hope that
this closed off city desperately
needs.
123:
Won't you join me in bringing
salvation to this world?
127:
...What kind of "salvation" are you
talking about?
131:
Why, peace, of course. The promise
of seeing a new dawn on the horizon.
133:
To do that, I'll need the strength to
banish the malignant powers that
bind the city. But you already know
that, don't you?
137:
To do anything, we'll need a specific
lance. It has the ability to connect
worlds.
140:
A lance? You wouldn't happen to be
talking about a long, black one,
would you?
143:
About a month ago, what appeared
to be a great bolt of lightning fell
from the sky...
147:
Many people, including myself, saw
a black lance within the light as it
descended.
150:
That was around the time the
people of Aegis first received their
powers as well. I suspect they might
know more than they let on—
154:
Why are you fighting Aegis in the
first place?
157:
Sure, they want to steal your food
and supplies, but that can't be the
only reason.
160:
It's a matter of principle, you see.
Their way of life is to take and take
until nothing is left but despair...
163:
Even a large organization like ours
has much to fear from unrelenting
greed.
166:
We have no choice but to fight if we
are to defend ourselves. But I believe
even they should be offered the
opportunity for salvation.
170:
...We'll help look for a way to escape
this place.
175:
We'll also help keep everyone in the
shelter safe, but that's all we can
promise for now.
179:
...That's more than enough. In time,
you shall see that we are worthy of
your trust.
184:
Sure... Well, we should be going.
Goodbye.
189:
By the way, I've prepared a room for
the two that you left behind in
Shibuya Station. They can hide there
instead.
192:
The people here who have been
waiting for salvation... might despair
that the outsiders that have come
are not the loved ones they've been
waiting for.
194:
Please, do watch out for yourselves.
I'll be praying for your safety.
